name: Jump!
description: Hop up to the sloper and mantle.

name: Whelmed
description: Start with a left hand high on a decent sidepull and right hand on a crimp.

name: Bubbles No-Hands
description: Climb the boulder with no hands!

name: No Pitons Here No-Hands
description: Climb the boulder with no hands!

name: Flying Goat Boy
description: Hop up to the sloper and mantle.

name: Schist Lip
description: Start sitting, rock over at the tree and continue diagonaling up or drop off.

name: Squatter Variation
description: Start with a high right hand on the arête and hop a foot up to the pimple.

name: Red Traverse
description: Traverse right, staying below the lip.

name: Fin Traverse
description: Start on the right side of the fin, shuffle to the left and then pull up to the main boulder, exiting near the top of The Pit.

name: Lowe Rider Stand
description: Traverse the detached flake, starting from a good left foot.

name: Joel’s Slab
description: Optional if you're up for it!

name: Lead Pants
description: Start sitting.

name: Royal Flush
description: Start deep in the cave.

name: Footless Traverse
description: An option hard and grand ending. Climb in 1 or 2 parts!

name: Lonely Fish
description: Use any means necessary to establish on the rail.

name: Sorrow Bird
description: Same start as Lonely Fish.

name: Old School
description: This one is tall but the hardest moves are low.

name: Bok Choy
description: Start with one had on the undercling.

name: Ice Age Left
description: Climb the left side of the arete - a lot easier than the original.

name: Answer Man
description: Sit start.

name: Nasty Boy
description: Climb right side of Bush Craft arete

name: Batman
description: The midday sun can make topping out this one feel a lot harder.

name: Down the Barrel
description: Optional if the water is low enough - could be a part of the official “Fall” version of the circuit

name: Heads Will Roll
description: Optional if the water is low enough.

name: The Rail
description: Sit start. Continue traversing left before topping out for some extra climbing.

name: Frosting
description: Climb up and right on the left arete.

name: Rainbow
description: Climb up and right on the steep side of the fin. Downclimb on the slabby side.

name: Breadline
description: Climb straight up or go out to the sloper and top out left.

name: Concavity Stand
description: Start in the crack and climb up and left. Or start on the sidepull left of the crack and climb straight up, eliminating the crack.

name: Power Steering
description: Sit start.

name: Portal Crack
description: Leads to the top of Moondog and Bad Moon Rising.

name: Redneck
description: Short slab.

name: Bad Moon Rising
description: Excellent technical slab with a committing move up high.

name: Dirty and Deep
description: Climb the low angle right arete.

name: Sunny and Steep
description: Climb the left side of the face on rounded jugs. Sit start.

name: Cleaver Crack
description: Start standing and climb the crack.

name: The Hobbit
description: Sit start.

name: Elfen Magic
description: Start in the middle of the slab with a good foothold and climb straight up.

name: Bowl Weevil
description: Start on the two edges in the overhang pull to the lip and top out.

name: Cornucopia
description: Start on head high jug and climb the arete up and left.

name: Terminal Traverse
description: Start where the lip is incut and traverse, mantling as for Playback.

name: Playback
description: Reach high to start with right in the crack and left on the face. Pad stacking to start helps.

name: Tron
description: Downclimb on the the other side of the tree.

name: Rainbow Crack
description: Optional. Climb the easy crack and walk down to Forestland parking.

name: The Shallow
description: Climb the tall face. Highball.

name: Cube Crack
description: Climb the tall crack. Highball.

name: The Cube
description: Work up crimps to a committing move to a jug. Highball.

name: Calcite
description: Start on the low edge and climb through crimps to calcite jug then up to top out right.

name: Pentaphobia
description: Start on any of the crimps and climb the sequential face.

name: Slice of Tea
description: Start between the boulders behind Pentaphobia and climb jugs out of the hole.

name: Gandalf
description: Start by laying back the central arete and then pull into the dihedral and work your way left to top out.

name: The Goods
description: Start from high edges on the right and traverse to the top of Crimp, Crimp.

name: Crimp, Crimp, Slab, Throw
description: Start on the two flat edges.

name: Funny and Cheap
description: Start as for Sunny and Steep but climb right through underclings then up.

name: The Physical
description: Reach high off the slab and pull into compression.

name: Toto
description: Sit start.

name: Arrested Development
description: Stand start and compress your way up and right. Trickier than it looks.

name: One Summer
description: Start standing on crimps and lunge to the good Breadline ledge. The crouch start adds a grade.

name: Squeezer
description: Stand start from the sidepull crimp.

name: Alcove Center
description: Start crouched on the big ledge and climb up to the jug and then top out up and left.

name: The Hesitator
description: Climb the tall slab with a probable moment of hesitation near the top.

name: Chunky
description: Traverse from a low undercling to the right with a final hard move down to the finish edge/jug.

name: Slice of Pie
description: Amazing boulder with a scary landing. Committing move up high.

name: Toprope Slab
description: Start just left of central blunt arete and work up and left to the left edge of the boulder.

name: Alfalfa or Spanky
description: Start on the head high edge and climb the dihedral.
